# Helm Template Patterns

## Helper Template Standards

All charts must define standard helpers in `_helpers.tpl`:

```yaml
{{/* Expand the name of the chart */}}
{{- define "chart-name.name" -}}
{{- default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix "-" }}
{{- end }}

{{/* Create a default fully qualified app name */}}
{{- define "chart-name.fullname" -}}
{{- if .Values.fullnameOverride }}
{{- .Values.fullnameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix "-" }}
{{- else }}
{{- $name := default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride }}
{{- if contains $name .Release.Name }}
{{- .Release.Name | trunc 63 | trimSuffix "-" }}
{{- else }}
{{- printf "%s-%s" .Release.Name $name | trunc 63 | trimSuffix "-" }}
{{- end }}
{{- end }}
{{- end }}

{{/* Common labels - REQUIRED */}}
{{- define "chart-name.labels" -}}
helm.sh/chart: {{ include "chart-name.chart" . }}
{{ include "chart-name.selectorLabels" . }}
{{- if .Chart.AppVersion }}
app.kubernetes.io/version: {{ .Chart.AppVersion | quote }}
{{- end }}
app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: {{ .Release.Service }}
{{- end }}

{{/* Selector labels - REQUIRED */}}
{{- define "chart-name.selectorLabels" -}}
app.kubernetes.io/name: {{ include "chart-name.name" . }}
app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}
{{- end }}
```

## Label Usage

Always use helper templates for labels:

```yaml
# ✅ GOOD
metadata:
  name: {{ include "chart-name.fullname" . }}
  labels:
    {{- include "chart-name.labels" . | nindent 4 }}

# ❌ BAD - hardcoded labels
metadata:
  name: my-app
  labels:
    app: my-app
```

## Selector Consistency

Use selectorLabels helper for consistency:

```yaml
# Deployment
spec:
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      {{- include "chart-name.selectorLabels" . | nindent 6 }}
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        {{- include "chart-name.selectorLabels" . | nindent 8 }}

# Service
spec:
  selector:
    {{- include "chart-name.selectorLabels" . | nindent 4 }}

# NetworkPolicy
spec:
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      {{- include "chart-name.selectorLabels" . | nindent 6 }}
```

## Conditional Resources

Use if/end for optional resources:

```yaml
{{- if .Values.ingress.enabled -}}
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: {{ include "chart-name.fullname" . }}
...
{{- end }}
```

## Indentation

Use `nindent` for proper YAML formatting:

```yaml
# ✅ GOOD
labels:
  {{- include "chart-name.labels" . | nindent 4 }}

# ❌ BAD - incorrect indentation
labels:
{{ include "chart-name.labels" . | indent 4 }}
```

## Value Access

Always provide defaults for optional values:

```yaml
# ✅ GOOD
replicas: {{ .Values.replicaCount | default 1 }}
port: {{ .Values.service.port | default 80 }}

# ✅ GOOD - with validation
{{- if not .Values.image.repository }}
{{- fail "image.repository is required" }}
{{- end }}
```

## String Quoting

Quote strings that might be interpreted as other types:

```yaml
# ✅ GOOD
version: {{ .Chart.AppVersion | quote }}
annotation: {{ .Values.annotation | quote }}

# Integers and booleans don't need quotes
replicas: {{ .Values.replicaCount }}
enabled: {{ .Values.ingress.enabled }}
```

## toYaml for Complex Structures

Use `toYaml` for nested structures:

```yaml
# ✅ GOOD
{{- if .Values.resources }}
resources:
  {{- toYaml .Values.resources | nindent 2 }}
{{- end }}

# ✅ GOOD - with custom egress rules
{{- if .Values.networkPolicy.egress.custom }}
{{- toYaml .Values.networkPolicy.egress.custom | nindent 2 }}
{{- end }}
```

## Resource Names

Always use fullname helper for resource names:

```yaml
metadata:
  name: {{ include "chart-name.fullname" . }}
  # For multiple resources of same type, add suffix:
  name: {{ include "chart-name.fullname" . }}-api
```

## Comments in Templates

Add comments for complex logic:

```yaml
{{/*
Allow ingress from nginx ingress controller.
Supports both namespace and pod selectors for flexibility.
*/}}
{{- if .Values.networkPolicy.ingress.enabled }}
...
{{- end }}
```
